Installation
Prerequisites
A modern web browser (Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge)
Internet connection to access the live demo or
A local server setup for running the game locally
Running Locally
Clone the Repository

sh
Copy code
git clone - https://mohitsharma7256.github.io/Tic-Tac-Toe-Game/
cd tic-tac-toe
Open the Index File
Simply open the index.html file in your web browser.

sh
Copy code
open index.html
or if you're using a local server setup (recommended for testing responsiveness):

sh
Copy code
# Example using Python's HTTP server
python3 -m http.server
# Open your browser and navigate to http://localhost:8000
Usage
Set Grid Size and Win Streak

Use the input fields to set the desired grid size (n x n) and the win streak (m).
Click the "Start Game" button to initialize the game board.
Play the Game

Click on any cell to mark it with 'X' or 'O'.
Players take turns until one player achieves the win streak or the game ends in a draw.
The game will display the result and provide an option to restart.
Code Structure
index.html: The main HTML file containing the structure of the game.
style.css: The CSS file for styling the game interface.
script.js: The JavaScript file containing the game logic.
